Interface PartialResultRetryPredicate<T,C extends Callable<? extends T>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BiFunction<T,C,RetryDecision<T,C>>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface PartialResultRetryPredicate<T,C extends Callable<? extends T>>
extends BiFunction<T,C,RetryDecision<T,C>>
    Chainable Result predicate. This predicate will not return a RetryDecision (null) when if want to deffer the retry decision.
